#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.26:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.26:0.2"
msgid "3. Anuttariyavagga"
msgstr "3. Unsurpassable"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.26:0.3"
msgid "26. Mahākaccānasutta"
msgstr "26. With Mahākaccāna"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā mahākaccāno bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Mahākaccāna addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.26:1.2"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an6.26:1.3"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākaccānassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an6.26:1.4"
msgid "Āyasmā mahākaccāno etadavoca:"
msgstr "Venerable Mahākaccāna said this:"

msgctxt "an6.26:1.5"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, āvuso;"
msgstr "“It’s incredible, reverends,"

msgctxt "an6.26:1.6"
msgid "abbhutaṃ, āvuso."
msgstr "it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an6.26:1.7"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sambādhe "
"okāsādhigamo anubuddho sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya "
"dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa "
"sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ cha anussatiṭṭhānāni."
msgstr ""
"How this Blessed One who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully "
"awakened Buddha, has found an opening in a confined space; that is, the six "
"topics for recollection. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get "
"past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to complete the "
"procedure, and to realize extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.315"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:2.1"
msgid "Katamāni cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.26:2.2"
msgid "Idhāvuso, ariyasāvako tathāgataṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple recollects the Realized One:"

msgctxt "an6.26:2.3"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an6.26:2.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye ariyasāvako tathāgataṃ anussarati nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the Realized One their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an6.26:2.5"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""
"At that time their mind is unswerving. They’ve left behind greed; they’re "
"free of it and have risen above it."

msgctxt "an6.26:2.6"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, āvuso, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Greed’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an6.26:2.7"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, āvuso, ariyasāvako sabbaso ākāsasamena cetasā viharati vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"That noble disciple meditates with a heart just like space, abundant, "
"expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an6.26:2.8"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, āvuso, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visuddhidhammā "
"bhavanti. (1)"
msgstr "Relying on this, some sentient beings have the factors for purity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, ariyasāvako dhammaṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects the teaching:"

msgctxt "an6.26:3.2"
msgid "‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo … pe … paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—realizable in this very life, "
"immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible "
"people can know it for themselves.’"

msgctxt "an6.26:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye ariyasāvako dhammaṃ anussarati nevassa tasmiṃ samaye "
"rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the teaching their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.26:3.4"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:3.5"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, āvuso, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:3.6"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, āvuso, ariyasāvako sabbaso ākāsasamena cetasā viharati vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:3.7"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, āvuso, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visuddhidhammā "
"bhavanti. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.316"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, ariyasāvako saṅghaṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects the Saṅgha:"

msgctxt "an6.26:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ "
"lokassā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, "
"straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the "
"eight individuals. This Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is worthy of "
"offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’"
"s offering, and worthy of veneration with joined palms. It is a supreme "
"field of merit for the world.’"

msgctxt "an6.26:4.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye ariyasāvako saṅghaṃ anussarati nevassa tasmiṃ samaye "
"rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the Saṅgha their mind is not full of greed, "
"hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.26:4.4"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:4.5"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, āvuso, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:4.6"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, āvuso, ariyasāvako sabbaso ākāsasamena cetasā viharati vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:4.7"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, āvuso, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visuddhidhammā "
"bhavanti. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, ariyasāvako attano sīlāni anussarati akhaṇḍāni … pe … "
"samādhisaṃvattanikāni."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects their own ethical precepts, which "
"are uncorrupted, unflawed, unblemished, untainted, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion."

msgctxt "an6.26:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye ariyasāvako attano sīlaṃ anussarati nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects their ethical precepts their mind is not "
"full of greed, hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.26:5.3"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:5.4"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, āvuso, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:5.5"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, āvuso, ariyasāvako sabbaso ākāsasamena cetasā viharati vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:5.6"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, āvuso, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visuddhidhammā "
"bhavanti. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, ariyasāvako attano cāgaṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects their own generosity:"

msgctxt "an6.26:6.2"
msgid "‘lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me … pe …"
msgstr "‘I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate!"

msgctxt "an6.26:6.3"
msgid "yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato’ti."
msgstr ""
"Among people full of the stain of stinginess I live at home rid of the stain "
"of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to "
"charity, loving to give and to share.’"

msgctxt "an6.26:6.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye ariyasāvako attano cāgaṃ anussarati nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects their own generosity their mind is not full "
"of greed, hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.26:6.5"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:6.6"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, āvuso, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:6.7"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, āvuso, ariyasāvako sabbaso ākāsasamena cetasā viharati vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.26:6.8"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, āvuso, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visuddhidhammā "
"bhavanti. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.317"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, ariyasāvako devatā anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects the deities:"

msgctxt "an6.26:7.2"
msgid "‘santi devā cātumahārājikā, santi devā … pe … tatuttari."
msgstr ""
"‘There are the Gods of the Four Great Kings, the Gods of the Thirty-Three, "
"the Gods of Yama, the Joyful Gods, the Gods Who Love to Create, the Gods Who "
"Control the Creations of Others, the Gods of Brahmā’s Group, and gods even "
"higher than these."

msgctxt "an6.26:7.3"
msgid "Yathārūpāya saddhāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tattha upapannā;"
msgstr ""
"When those deities passed away from here, they were reborn there because of "
"their faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom."

msgctxt "an6.26:7.4"
msgid ""
"mayhampi tathārūpā saddhā saṃvijjati. Yathārūpena sīlena … sutena … cāgena … "
"paññāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tattha upapannā; mayhampi tathārūpā "
"paññā saṃvijjatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I, too, have the same kind of faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and "
"wisdom.’"

msgctxt "an6.26:7.5"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye ariyasāvako attano ca tāsañca devatānaṃ saddhañca "
"sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarati nevassa tasmiṃ samaye "
"rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom of both themselves and the deities their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an6.26:7.6"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""
"At that time their mind is unswerving. They’ve left behind greed; they’re "
"free of it and have risen above it."

msgctxt "an6.26:7.7"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, āvuso, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Greed’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an6.26:7.8"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, āvuso, ariyasāvako sabbaso ākāsasamena cetasā viharati vipulena "
"mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena."
msgstr ""
"That noble disciple meditates with a heart just like space, abundant, "
"expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an6.26:7.9"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, āvuso, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visuddhidhammā "
"bhavanti. (6)"
msgstr "Relying on this, some sentient beings have the factors for purity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.26:8.1"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso."
msgstr "It’s incredible, reverends, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an6.26:8.2"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sambādhe "
"okāsādhigamo anubuddho sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya "
"dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa "
"sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ cha anussatiṭṭhānānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"How this Blessed One who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully "
"awakened Buddha, has found an opening in a confined space; that is, the six "
"topics for recollection. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get "
"past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to complete the "
"procedure, and to realize extinguishment.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.26:8.3"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
